    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Original, rudimentary plows without mouldboards that are pulled by pack animals. It turns up but does not invert the soil, as opposed to the later turnplow.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000092503/Encyclopedia of Indo-European Culture J.P. Mallory, D.Q. Adams 1997  435</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oorspronkelijke, simpele ploeg zonder strijkbord die getrokken wordt door lastdieren en de grond loswoelt, maar niet omkeert zoals de latere keerploeg.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
